<protolog id="rid.2250_nm.9571" type="description" xmlns="http://namesforlife.com/ns/protolog" xmlns:xsi="http://www.w3.org/2001/XMLSchema-instance" xsi:schemaLocation="http://namesforlife.com/ns/protolog file:/C:/NamesforLife/workspace/namesforlife-schema/protolog.xsd"><organism doi="10.1601/nm.9571" rank="genus">Thalassobacillus</organism><reference id="rid.2250"><citation citation-type="journal"><authors><person-name><surname>García</surname><given-names>M.T.</given-names></person-name><person-name><surname>Gallego</surname><given-names>V.</given-names></person-name><person-name><surname>Ventosa</surname><given-names>A.</given-names></person-name><person-name><surname>Mellado</surname><given-names>E.</given-names></person-name></authors><article-title>Thalassobacillus devorans gen. nov., sp. nov., a moderately halophilic, phenol-degrading, Gram-positive bacterium</article-title><year>2005</year><volume>55</volume><issue>5</issue><fpage>1789</fpage><lpage>1795</lpage><source id="117">International Journal of Systematic and Evolutionary Microbiology</source><abbrev>Int J Syst Evol Microbiol</abbrev><issn>1466-5026</issn><essn>1466-5034</essn><pub-id pub-id-type="doi">10.1099/ijs.0.63560-0</pub-id><pub-id pub-id-type="pmid">16166667</pub-id></citation></reference><content><p class="title"><s>Description of <em>Thalassobacillus</em> gen. nov.</s></p><p class="etymology"><s><em>Thalassobacillus</em> (Tha.las′so.ba.cil′lus. Gr. fem. n. <em>thalassa</em> sea; L. masc. n. <em>bacillus</em> rod; N.L. masc. n. <em>Thalassobacillus</em> rod from the sea).</s></p><p class="description"><s>Gram-positive, spore-forming, rod-shaped cells.</s><s>Motile.</s><s>Catalase-positive, oxidase-negative and urease-negative.</s><s>Nitrate is reduced to nitrite.</s><s>Ellipsoidal endospores in central position.</s><s>Moderately halophilic: does not grow in media without NaCl.</s><s>Cell-wall peptidoglycan type A1<em>γ</em> with <em>m</em>-Dpm.</s><s>Major fatty acids are anteiso-C<sub>15 : 0</sub>, iso-C<sub>16 : 0</sub> and iso-C<sub>15 : 0</sub>.</s><s>Predominant menaquinone is MK-7.</s><s>The G+C content of the DNA of the type species is 42·4 mol%.</s><s>The type species is <em>Thalassobacillus devorans</em>.</s></p></content></protolog>